.TH "nvme_create_ctrl" 9 "nvme_create_ctrl" "March 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvme_create_ctrl \- Allocate an unconnected NVMe controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nvme_create_ctrl
.BI "(struct nvme_global_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "const char *subsysnqn "  ","
.BI "const char *transport "  ","
.BI "const char *traddr "  ","
.BI "const char *host_traddr "  ","
.BI "const char *host_iface "  ","
.BI "const char *trsvcid "  ","
.BI "nvme_ctrl_t *c "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
struct nvme_global_ctx object
.IP "subsysnqn" 12
Subsystem NQN
.IP "transport" 12
Transport type
.IP "traddr" 12
Transport address
.IP "host_traddr" 12
Host transport address
.IP "host_iface" 12
Host interface name
.IP "trsvcid" 12
Transport service ID
.IP "c" 12
\fInvme_ctrl_t\fP object to return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates an unconnected controller to be used for \fBnvme_add_ctrl\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or negative error code otherwise
